Man: "What is this in the world?"
Rogers: "It's a Geiger counter, which is used to locate radioactive minerals, such as uranium.
When you wear these earbuds, you can hear the effects of the atoms emitted by the radioactivity of the minerals."
Evans: "Say, sure it's bursting now!"
"Hans" Geiger died in 1945, just days after his 63rd birthday.
