Bat populations in Scotland and throughout the United Kingdom have declined considerably over the past century.
These animals are threatened by construction and development works that affect nests and habitat loss.
Wind turbines and lighting also pose a risk, as do traps with glue for flies, some chemical treatments of building materials, and attacks from domestic cats.
